Mercury has so much charm and is PERFECT for date night! They have these cute little areas and the drinks are fun and delicious! I recommend highly!

I can't say too much about the place as my sister works here but, I can't say I have ever been disappointed by the service and there menu is very interesting, at the moment they are doing a chose your own adventure to figure out what kind of drink you want, but you can skip pg46 if you don't want to do that, past that they have a really nice selection of liquor, and the bartender's know a thing or two making a drink so if you want to go off script they can oblige, oh and they normally have a kitchen that makes pretty good food, although it's mainly small plates or "share ables", anyway I over all I would like to say it's worth checking out

Cool atmosphere, great staff and creative drinks. A whole story line to figure out the best drink to order.

Service is outstanding. Menu was a choose your own adventure book which was extremely creative and fun. Meat and cheese board was delicious. The cocktails where delicious and unique. If cocktails aren't your think the spirit list is the best in Omaha. The Wine list is also impressive.
Music was fantastic - service food and drinks well provided.

I absolutely love this place! They make the cutest cocktails during the winter. They go above and beyond for every drink they make. Truly a delight each time I drink there. Caution to those who want cheaper drinks: this is NOT the place to go. They serve quality liquor that will be costly. Worth the money!  5/5
Wow.  Just wow
Love this place. Love the drinks.  Had so much fun giving the bartender mini challenges... he did fantastic too!   Nice atmosphere, great staff, excellent food.  Will make it a point to be back!
Great food, great drinks, and the themed nights are awesome!
I absolutely love this place! Friendly staff, great drinks! reasonable prices. Really cool menu! 10/10

I really enjoyed this atmosphere. Quiet and comfy with the right amount of noise. Great place for friends to meet up or I'm sure even first dates. Cocktails are truly amazing. Their whiskey and bourbon collection is also quite impressive. Not too many places carry Blanton's!

Our cocktails here we good, but the food was frankly overpriced and underwhelming. If they simply lowered the prices the food would be good. We paid $8 for 3 very small ravioli with only a carrot puree inside. We also got the fondue which was more than $10 for what seemed to be about 1/2 cup of processed runny cheese and some very run of the mill crostini.  Great atmosphere and friendly staff - but stick to the drinks.

Mercury is open late, which is one it’s main calling points. I’ve been here twice, once for drinks and once for food and drinks. I like the food more then the cocktails, tried a few things including the chicken on a biscuit, it’s all fine, nothing really special or amazing. The drinks I find far too sweet, having tried 3-4 cocktails. Would look elsewhere if you can.

Cocktails are so well put together, changing from season to season. Always nice to try a flavor of the moment or have a classic. Food is good and the bartenders are all so nice! I would recommend, def be careful since it is not exactly budget friendly. A splurge for sure and worth it.
Great food, atmosphere and people.
Interesting lounge

Cocktails were great but the food was very disappointing. The high prices did not reflect the quality of the food. $12 Chicken on a Biscuit was soggy and fell apart in my hands. We suspected it was microwaved. We’re also pretty sure the chips served on the side were sour cream & onion Ruffles that we could have bought at the C store across the street. The pasta we had was okay but for the price we paid, we expected it to at least be warm and not be over cooked. Three of the entrees were also not available, including the chicken dish which reinforced our suspicion that our chicken sandwich was just pulled out of the fridge and microwaved. Our opinion: Focus on the great cocktails and just have some unique snack options, not entrees.

This is a cute, cozy spot downtown. I am impressed with their signature cocktail menu; although, it was rather difficult to choose. I find it absolutely lovely and cheeky how they pair the brasserie to the cocktail, and I think you will too. I found my cocktail to be a bit strong, but I suppose I'm the only person who will complain of something like this. There was quite the crowd on a Saturday night, so be prepared to wait or to arrive slightly early to meet with your group.

Absolutely love the Mercury! The mid-century decor and modern alternative music selection are a perfect match. Service is excellent and the staff are amiable. Plus, the specialty cocktails have an extra cool factor on account of the clinebell ice machine they use to get crystal clear ice chunks. This is my favorite place to end a night out in Omaha.
Staff is more concerned with doing shots amongst themselves. Then helping customers. They charged us for drinks we didn't have.  Probably to pay for the shots. Over priced and over rated.

Creative cocktails served with the best ice cubes I've ever seen, chainsawed and chiseled off a 300-pound block of ice produced in house. The care given to the ice in your drink speaks volumes about the care that goes into everything else.

Food and drinks are good, and the drink selection is very good. However, our server did a poor job getting our orders out in a timely manner. She must have completely forgotten my food order, as I waited for nearly a half hour before reminding her, then it was out in only a few minutes. She also forgot to bring out another individual's drink, while charging it to the bill and taking payment for it. We had to remind her about the drink as well. And despite these issues, we were charged an automatic 20% gratuity for a larger party. The establishment was not busy and I cannot account for the poor service. I left feeling unsatisfied, as did most of the group.

Mercury is a chic downtown bar. I was there for the Traveling Dundee book library, and a writer's signing. Furniture is relaxing and comfortable. Location was very clean and well-light. Drink prices seemed to be about in line with the rest of downtown Omaha. The design seems very pinteresty, which is fine, but will probably be out-dated within 5 years.
Great bar with amazing drinks. The selection of craft cocktails is incredible. Can't wait to go back and try more.

Mercury is one of the best cocktail bars in Omaha. It is one of my go-to places for a nice drink and maybe a small bite to eat. Their wine and spirits selection is top of the line and their empanadas are perfect! I highly recommend the tiramisu as well, one of the best I have ever had.
Fun cocktails, fun staff, great food!

Great cocktails and an amazing selection of whiskey as well. Lots of tapas style food all is great for sharing. The staff are incredibly friendly and helpful especially if you'd like to explore new whiskeys.  Can't recommend this place enough. Definitely a most try for Omaha.
Drinks and food are great. Bartenders are welcoming and knowledgeable.  They down sized the food menu a bit but food (even served late night) is still great. We will be back.

This is a great place for cocktails and small plates. The food is good, fresh, and quite fast. Happy hour is a wonderful time to come try several different menu items, food and drink. The small plates are great for ordering two or three different items and sharing. The cocktails will not disappoint. Although it can get spendy, they are worth it to try a couple. The staff are knowledgeable and friendly, and love to discuss the cocktails, food, or the latest event coming up. The decor is a cozy mid century lounge with armchairs and couches, as well as tables. Great views of downtown with plenty of people watching outside the giant picture windows!
This is a fantastic place with unique drink options. The mid-century modern theming carries through the drink and food menu! Great bonus that the kitchen is open until 2am!
Great atmosphere. Superb cocktails. Fantastic service. Delicious food.  Don't know what else I can say.  It's a perfect little spot downtown.
Great service that helps you find a great cocktail for yourself. Chill and relaxing atmosphere.
A relaxing atmosphere with attractive decor. Drinks and food are amazing. Great service.

Wonderful mixology and inventive dishes that change seasonally. Friendly environment. A very modern design in a repurposed space. I personally love that they took the old walk in safe (this used to be a jewelry store) and turned it into their wine cellar.
No service.  Not poor service, NO service!!  But, we only waited 15 minutes for a server...
Great drinks.  Such a relaxing and unique vibe.  The food was spectacular.  The staff was wonderful.  A favorite of Omaha, for sure.

First thing is first - GO HERE - more details below,  but great drinks, good food, staff, and location.  Stopped in last night (2/22) to have drinks and food prior to the game. 8 of us came in and took up 2 couches and some seats.  The waiter we had was attentive, knew the food and described it well when arrived and ordered.  My family enjoyed the Mexican Mules(Moscow mules with tequila) and a few others enjoyed the 38 special, which i HIGHLY recommend getting if you like bourbon.   After the meal the waiter gave my dad the name of the cherries they use in that drink, and he let my GF and I sit around and relax after the group left.  The vibe is great, the staff seems friendly.  Even the bartender came over to make sure the drinks everyone got was what they wanted.  To make it even better, the only thing that bothered our group was there was a woman/waitress at the bar with her laptop open doing something, and occasionally would come out to tables to drop off drinks or say hi.  Seemed out of place, and she really didn't seem happy to be there.
Great cocktails! Love the old safe in the back. Wonderful customer service.
Great drink menu, Great environment, Great food. Service was great as well.
Drinks bitter but appetizers greatand atmosphese cool hang out

My friend and I walked in and went to the back to use the restroom. No one said anything to us, so we simply walked back and did what we needed. We were taking a break from my sisters bachelorette party and about to start up on our scavenger hunt again. When I came out of the bathroom, there was a lady put there who looked like the manager. She come right up to my face and says "We're you actually planning on buying something, or were you just using us like some public bathroom?" I was shocked. They didn't have any signs saying bathrooms were for customers only, and they had said nothing to us when we walked in. We were planning on having some small appetizers and getting a table together to celebrate. I told the lady kindly that we were sorry, but we no one told us, to which she glared at me and nudged her head at the door. She didn't even offer us a table (many of which were open) or ask us if we were interested in staying. She didn't even let me say whether we were going to buy something or not, and then my friend came out, so we left. I won't go back, and I wouldn't want any of my friends to go back their either. Not worth the food or drinks for the service.
Staff was friendly and helpful, the cocktails were outstanding! Just a touch pricy.
